like crap ♪

02:43.772 --> 02:46.035
♪ It's time to face the fact

02:46.078 --> 02:47.167
♪ It's your prerogative

02:47.210 --> 02:49.560
♪ Your prerogative♪

02:49.604 --> 02:51.867
♪ To be positive

02:51.910 --> 02:54.609
♪ If we become ♪ If we become♪

02:54.652 --> 02:56.654
♪ What we believe ♪ What we believe♪

02:56.698 --> 02:59.831
♪ Then as ye think
ye shall receive ♪♪ As ye think♪

02:59.875 --> 03:02.312
♪ So just let go of the past♪♪ So let go of the past

03:02.356 --> 03:05.185
♪ Pull your head from your ass

03:05.228 --> 03:06.751
♪ It's your prerogative

03:06.795 --> 03:09.058
♪ Your prerogative♪

03:09.101 --> 03:10.842
♪ To be positive.

03:21.636 --> 03:24.334
Oh! 90 miles
to Louisville.

03:24.378 --> 03:26.423
Lou-uh-ville.What?

03:26.467 --> 03:28.947
You're saying it wrong.
It's... Lou-uh-ville.

03:28.991 --> 03:30.514
Louis-ville.

03:30.558 --> 03:32.821
J-Just throw it away.
Louisville.

03:32.864 --> 03:34.649
[with accent]:
Louisville! Ooh.

03:34.692 --> 03:36.346
I don't know why I did
an Italian accent there.

03:36.390 --> 03:37.391
I panicked.

03:37.434 --> 03:39.219
[alert dings]Uh-oh.

03:39.262 --> 03:41.612
The "Check Engine" light just
came on. What do we do?

03:41.656 --> 03:43.527
Well, here's a thought.
We check the engine.

03:43.571 --> 03:46.051
Oh, God! Oh, God.

03:46.095 --> 03:48.706
Oh, no! There was
a fire extinguisher in the back

03:48.750 --> 03:51.361
but I got rid of it to
make room for my K-Cups.

03:51.405 --> 03:53.537
It's just overheating.
Just pull over.

03:53.581 --> 03:56.236
Where's the hazard lights?

03:56.279 --> 03:58.150
Nope-- oh, nope.

03:58.194 --> 04:01.241
Oh, boy, I'm really doing
the wrong thing here.

04:02.459 --> 04:04.069
[knocks]Hello!

04:04.113 --> 04:06.550
Oh, hey.Looking for a lawyer?

04:06.594 --> 04:10.728
I present my son,
Kyle Morgan, attorney at law.

04:10.772 --> 04:11.686
Nice to meet you.

04:11.729 --> 04:13.514
Hi.At the risk of overstating

04:13.557 --> 04:15.559
his legal skills,
imagine Matlock

04:15.603 --> 04:17.822
rebooted with Michael B. Jordan.

04:17.866 --> 04:18.606
Dad...

04:18.649 --> 04:19.781
He also plays clarinet.

04:19.824 --> 04:20.869
Dad!

04:20.912 --> 04:23.263
You take good care of her,
Bubbaroo.

04:23.306 --> 04:25.047
[laughs]

04:25.090 --> 04:26.962
Hmm. Bubbaroo?

04:27.005 --> 04:28.572
He's called me that
since I was a baby.

04:28.616 --> 04:30.748
It's a whole thing.
There's even a song.

04:30.792 --> 04:31.836
Really?

04:31.880 --> 04:33.403
Oh, he'll sing it for you.
Just ask.

04:33.447 --> 04:35.362
I'd rather hear you play it
on your clarinet.

04:35.405 --> 04:37.755
Have a seat, Bubbaroo.

04:37.799 --> 04:40.018
So, why do you
need a lawyer?

04:40.062 --> 04:41.411
My dad didn't give me
any details.

04:41.455 --> 04:43.674
Oh, it's embarrassing.

04:43.718 --> 04:45.415
Tell me, I won't judge.

04:45.459 --> 04:47.287
Okay...

04:47.330 --> 04:50.942
a few years ago I got busted
for selling fake IDs to kids.

04:50.986 --> 04:52.770
Not that bad.Then I missed my court date.

04:52.814 --> 04:54.424
Okay.Then I paid the fine
with a phony check.

04:54.468 --> 04:56.426
All right.Then I stole the identity

04:56.470 --> 04:58.515
of a woman who died in 1951.

04:59.168 --> 05:02.127
Kind of feels like you're
judging me, Bubbaroo.

05:02.171 --> 05:03.128
Little bit.

05:03.172 --> 05:04.391
I promise

05:04.434 --> 05:05.783
I am a completely
different person now.

05:05.827 --> 05:08.612
You know that all criminals
say that, right?

05:08.656 --> 05:12.007
I've got a friend at the
DA's office, let me get into it.

05:12.050 --> 05:15.315
Okay.In the meantime, if you need me.

05:15.358 --> 05:17.229
Thank you. Oh, oh!

05:17.273 --> 05:18.753
I knew you looked familiar.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.755
I've seen your ads on
buses and billboards.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.974
"If you've gotta go to trial,
call Kyle."

05:23.018 --> 05:24.149
"I'll get you off!"

05:24.193 --> 05:25.368
Didn't hear the double meaning

05:25.412 --> 05:26.674
till it was too late.

05:27.414 --> 05:29.503
Well, I love it.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.983
I sat on your face
at a bus stop.

05:34.464 --> 05:35.552
[sportscaster speaking
indistinctly]

05:35.596 --> 05:37.075
Ah!Oh!

05:37.119 --> 05:39.121
Fourth and three with less
than two minutes left

05:39.164 --> 05:40.731
and you're gonna punt?

05:40.775 --> 05:43.778
They deserve to lose. How is he
still their head coach?

05:43.821 --> 05:45.823
I mean, they can't stop
the double-A gap blitz;

05:45.867 --> 05:48.043
of course
they're gonna punt.

05:48.086 --> 05:49.653
You know football?

05:49.697 --> 05:51.263
Yeah, I played in college.

05:51.307 --> 05:53.048
You did? What position?

05:53.091 --> 05:54.136
Seated.

05:55.746 --> 05:58.967
I played Madden.
It's a video game.

05:59.707 --> 06:01.665
I was almost impressed with you.

06:02.449 --> 06:04.712
Norma, I have some
ibuprofen for you.

06:04.755 --> 06:08.106
You better have something
stronger. My hip is killing me.

06:08.150 --> 06:09.673
Uh, how about an ice pack?

06:09.717 --> 06:11.501
Uh, how about this?

06:11.545 --> 06:12.676
What are you doing?

06:12.720 --> 06:15.679
Flipping you off with arthritis.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.378
If I was
controlling that guy,

06:18.421 --> 06:20.597
I'd call
a run-pass option,

06:20.641 --> 06:24.558
roll out left
and then hit the C button.

06:25.428 --> 06:28.953
I don't know whether to buy you
a beer or give you a wedgie.

06:30.085 --> 06:34.481
Of course it's a word.
It's the past tense for "twit."

06:34.524 --> 06:36.265
Hello, everyone.Hey, Bette.

06:36.308 --> 06:37.484
Spencer.

06:37.527 --> 06:38.572
Hello.

06:38.615 --> 06:39.573
How have you been?

06:39.616 --> 06:41.096
Oh, good, thanks.

06:42.967 --> 06:45.056
You know, I-I think I gotta go.

06:45.100 --> 06:48.408
I got to call a guy about
a thing I need him to do

06:48.451 --> 06:50.671
for me over in the room here...

06:51.933 --> 06:55.197
There's no guy.
His Metamucil kicked in.

06:56.633 --> 06:58.592
Ever since our date,
he's been avoiding me.

06:58.635 --> 07:00.507
Has he said anything?

07:00.550 --> 07:03.161
He might have.
I try not to listen.

07:03.205 --> 07:05.990
I don't understand. No man
has ever rejected me like this.

07:06.774 --> 07:08.732
Norma, how do you handle it?

07:13.607 --> 07:15.696
Uh, water pump's shot.

07:15.739 --> 07:18.046
We know. That's
why we're here.

07:18.089 --> 07:21.571
And we appreciate everything
that you're doing...

07:21.615 --> 07:23.921
Roy.Roy. Right.

07:23.965 --> 07:25.793
Is that your dog outside, Roy?

07:25.836 --> 07:28.448
What a cutie, even
without teeth.

07:28.491 --> 07:31.712
And just the one eye there.

07:31.755 --> 07:34.497
Parts and labor, it's gonna
run you around two grand.

07:34.541 --> 07:38.109
[sighs, whoops]

07:38.153 --> 07:41.809
Stinky. Um, two large.

07:41.852 --> 07:43.375
Ugh. Not you, the cost.

07:43.419 --> 07:46.074
You are actually quite svelte.

07:46.117 --> 07:49.294
What do you do, what are we,
in SoulCycle? Peloton?

07:49.338 --> 07:50.687
We're leaving.What?

07:50.731 --> 07:52.602
Come on. We can do it ourselves.

07:52.646 --> 07:55.126
We passed an auto parts store
on our way here.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.737
Can you give us a second,
please?

07:56.780 --> 07:59.783
Sure. I'll be on my Peloton.

07:59.827 --> 08:03.526
[laughs]:
Oh, yes, right, from earlier.

08:03.570 --> 08:05.920
Um, what are you doing?

08:05.963 --> 08:07.312
I don't know
how to fix an engine.

08:07.356 --> 08:09.837
You don't say. Let's go.

08:09.880 --> 08:12.361
No, look, look,
I know it's expensive,

08:12.404 --> 08:13.971
but I got a good feeling
about Roy.

08:14.015 --> 08:15.451
I mean, they wouldn't make
his garage the post office

08:15.495 --> 08:17.714
if he wasn't
a stand-up guy.

08:17.758 --> 08:21.196
I'm telling you,
we can do it ourselves.

08:22.197 --> 08:23.981
Fine.

08:24.852 --> 08:28.986
Roy, uh, we're gonna pass
on the water pump,

08:29.030 --> 08:32.729
but I will take two books
of Forever stamps.

08:35.689 --> 08:36.646
[knocking]

08:36.690 --> 08:38.213
Who is it?Kyle!

08:38.256 --> 08:39.519
[gasps] Damn it.

08:39.562 --> 08:42.609
Peter's son, the lawyer?

08:42.652 --> 08:44.654
One minute!

08:49.572 --> 08:51.574
[clears throat]
Come in!

08:51.618 --> 08:53.489
Hey.One sec. I'm just

08:53.533 --> 08:57.232
finishing up some important
work things. [clears throat]

08:57.275 --> 09:00.191
Approved, approved.

09:00.235 --> 09:01.889
Denied.

09:02.629 --> 09:04.674
[sighs]
What's up?

09:04.718 --> 09:05.936
I'm here to see my dad,

09:05.980 --> 09:08.069
and I got some good news
about your case.

09:08.112 --> 09:11.681
Wow, no lawyer has ever
said that to me.

09:11.725 --> 09:13.683
Talked to my buddy
at the DA's office.

09:13.727 --> 09:14.945
You're looking at a fine

09:14.989 --> 09:17.557
and 30 hours
of community service.

09:17.600 --> 09:19.428
That's so great.

09:19.471 --> 09:20.690
Thank you so much.

09:20.734 --> 09:22.692
It was nothing.
You should see

09:22.736 --> 09:24.259
some of the people I represent.

09:24.302 --> 09:25.869
Hey, what do I owe you?

09:25.913 --> 09:27.697
Don't worry about it. I just
made a few of phone calls.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.830
No, that's crazy.

09:29.873 --> 09:32.702
Look, you are so great
with my dad.

09:33.573 --> 09:35.009
Let's just call it even.Come on.

09:35.052 --> 09:36.314
I insist.

09:36.358 --> 09:37.925
All right, how about this?

09:37.968 --> 09:41.102
You take me out
for a nice dinner.

09:41.145 --> 09:43.234
Oh. Dinner.

09:43.278 --> 09:45.715
Or not. I don't want to
put you on the spot.

09:45.759 --> 09:48.413
No, um, I would like that.

09:48.457 --> 09:50.372
How's Friday?Great.

09:50.415 --> 09:51.852
See you then.

09:51.895 --> 09:53.593
Okay. I'd walk
you out, but...

09:53.636 --> 09:56.683
I'm pretty busy here.

10:00.469 --> 10:04.168
The next thing we need to do
is remove the cooling fan.

10:04.212 --> 10:05.909
You know,
if I were Harry Potter,

10:05.953 --> 10:08.259
I would just say
"Remov-io Fan-io."

10:08.303 --> 10:09.870
[laughs]

10:09.913 --> 10:11.611
You know, this is your van.
You should learn how to do this.

10:11.654 --> 10:12.655
Why?

10:12.699 --> 10:13.700
I can just hire someone

10:13.743 --> 10:14.875
who knows what they're doing.

10:14.918 --> 10:16.659
I mean,
I don't cut my own hair.

10:16.703 --> 10:19.314
Yeah, whoever cuts your hair
doesn't know what they're doing.

10:20.532 --> 10:22.665
Someday you'll wish
you'd learned how to,

10:22.709 --> 10:24.624
how to take a--Oh...

10:24.667 --> 10:25.625
Oh, damn it.

10:25.668 --> 10:26.626
You okay?

10:26.669 --> 10:28.453
No, it's my back.

10:28.497 --> 10:31.108
Okay, well, sit down.[groans]

10:31.152 --> 10:31.979
What happened?

10:32.022 --> 10:33.633
It's an old sports injury.

10:33.676 --> 10:35.635
You wouldn't understand.

10:36.461 --> 10:38.289
Is there anything I can do?

10:38.333 --> 10:40.509
I just need to rest.

10:40.552 --> 10:42.685
[exhales]
You'll have to take over.

10:42.729 --> 10:45.688
What? No.Come on.

10:45.732 --> 10:47.472
I'll talk you through it.Oh, come on.

10:47.516 --> 10:50.693
I'll just mess it up. Let's
just take it back to the garage.

10:50.737 --> 10:52.956
Okay. Okay.
You just have to

10:53.000 --> 10:55.002
put the engine back together.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.397
Check and mate.

11:00.224 --> 11:02.313
Okay, well, let me
at least put on an apron.

11:02.357 --> 11:04.315
My Tide stick
is down to the nub.

11:07.492 --> 11:09.016
Ow. Gabby,

11:09.059 --> 11:11.018
what do you know
about CBD oil?

11:11.061 --> 11:14.151
Save your money.
It doesn't get you high.

11:14.195 --> 11:15.805
Hi.

11:15.849 --> 11:17.328
Peter's son was looking for you.

11:17.372 --> 11:20.767
Oh, yeah, we were just in
my office. He got me off!

11:20.810 --> 11:22.986
Isn't it way
hotter at work?

11:23.030 --> 11:27.861
Not that. Although he
did ask me to dinner.

11:27.904 --> 11:31.647
Oh, I thought you were
giving up dating for a while.

11:31.691 --> 11:34.476
I know. I am. I was.

11:34.519 --> 11:36.173
Oh, he's so cute.

11:37.522 --> 11:38.915
What about Drew?

11:38.959 --> 11:41.004
Oh, well, Drew's off
living his van life.

11:41.048 --> 11:43.006
And he already slept
with some rando.

11:43.050 --> 11:47.663
And he should because
we are not a thing.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.839
We never were, we never will be.

11:49.883 --> 11:51.754
Friends, yes.

11:51.798 --> 11:54.714
Maybe one drunken kiss,
but that's it.

11:54.757 --> 11:56.672
Over and out.
[imitates static]

11:56.716 --> 11:58.500
Done and done.

12:00.632 --> 12:01.764
Interesting.

12:01.808 --> 12:02.765
Very.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.941
It's not interesting!

12:04.985 --> 12:07.248
Oh, hey, Peter.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.989
Oh, hello. Hey,

12:09.032 --> 12:11.818
Kyle tells me that your
legal woes are no more.

12:11.861 --> 12:13.863
Oh, he did a great job.

12:13.907 --> 12:15.212
I'm gonna take him to dinner
to thank him.

12:15.256 --> 12:17.562
Wonderful. Will Holly
be joining you?

12:17.606 --> 12:18.825
Holly?

12:18.868 --> 12:21.479
Kyle's wife. She's an angel.

12:21.523 --> 12:23.655
He's married?Yes.

12:23.699 --> 12:24.961
She teaches kindergarten--

12:25.005 --> 12:27.790
a time of wonder
and exploration.

12:27.834 --> 12:29.270
And also lice.

12:36.277 --> 12:36.930
Hey.

12:36.973 --> 12:38.018
Hey, close the door.

12:38.061 --> 12:39.802
No, with you inside.

12:39.846 --> 12:41.935
Oh, fun.

12:42.805 --> 12:44.198
Kyle is married.

12:44.241 --> 12:46.722
What?Yes, to a kindergarten teacher.

12:46.766 --> 12:47.941
Peter told me.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.725
How could he ask me out
on a date?

12:49.769 --> 12:51.031
Guys are the worst!

12:51.074 --> 12:52.597
I am gonna call
him on it.

12:52.641 --> 12:55.557
Who would cheat
on a kindergarten teacher?

12:55.600 --> 12:56.950
That poor woman.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.821
Not being smart enough
to teach grade school,

12:58.865 --> 13:01.302
and now this.

13:02.607 --> 13:04.392
[phone ringing]

13:04.435 --> 13:06.916
