courthouse so I might lose you.

13:06.960 --> 13:08.004
What's up?

13:08.048 --> 13:10.398
Oh, there is a lot up, Kyle.

13:10.441 --> 13:12.008
There is a lot up.

13:12.922 --> 13:14.097
What?

13:14.141 --> 13:15.969
How dare you ask me out.
You are married.

13:16.012 --> 13:17.840
No, I'm not.Oh, please.

13:17.884 --> 13:20.277
Your dad told me
all about Holly.

13:20.321 --> 13:22.845
We're gonna send you her head
in a box!

13:22.889 --> 13:24.151
What? No.

13:24.194 --> 13:25.848
We are-- no,
we are not gonna do that.

13:25.892 --> 13:27.328
We are definitely
not doing that.

13:28.068 --> 13:30.374
Holly and I divorced
three years ago.

13:30.418 --> 13:32.159
Oh.

13:33.421 --> 13:39.166
Oh. Your dad
still thinks you're married.

13:39.209 --> 13:40.602
Damn.

13:40.645 --> 13:42.996
His memory's gotten worse over
the last few years,

13:43.039 --> 13:45.259
but this is scary.Yeah.

13:45.302 --> 13:48.044
We see this here all the time.

13:48.958 --> 13:53.441
There's some things we can do
to help make his life easier.

13:53.484 --> 13:54.790
Thank you.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.531
I can talk to him if you'd like.

13:56.574 --> 13:58.054
That would be great.

13:58.098 --> 14:00.752
Okay. I'll let you know
what I find out.

14:00.796 --> 14:02.189
Please do.

14:05.192 --> 14:08.543
Peter forgot his son
is divorced.

14:08.586 --> 14:10.197
That's not good.

14:10.240 --> 14:11.676
Poor guy.

14:11.720 --> 14:12.939
Bright side--

14:12.982 --> 14:15.202
Kyle's single!

14:17.508 --> 14:20.468
Okay, next thing, before
you take out the water pump,

14:20.511 --> 14:22.339
you've gotta remove
the mounting bolts.

14:22.383 --> 14:25.255
You mean the things that look
like Frankenstein's neck?

14:25.299 --> 14:27.344
Yes, just like the hose clamp

14:27.388 --> 14:29.172
looked like
a friendship bracelet.

14:29.216 --> 14:30.565
Tell me it doesn't.

14:33.133 --> 14:34.830
Which way do I turn
this thing again?

14:34.874 --> 14:37.877
[groans]
Righty tighty, lefty loosey.

14:37.920 --> 14:39.791
See, that doesn't
make sense to me

14:39.835 --> 14:41.141
because the first half rhymes,

14:41.184 --> 14:42.533
and the second half
is alliterative.

14:42.577 --> 14:44.361
I mean, how is anyone
gonna remember that?

14:44.405 --> 14:46.015
[groans]

14:46.059 --> 14:48.191
[grunts] It won't move.

14:48.235 --> 14:49.497
Put some muscle into it.

14:49.540 --> 14:51.542
Oh, damn it!

14:51.586 --> 14:53.893
See, I told you
I was no good at this.

14:53.936 --> 14:55.024
You can learn.

14:55.068 --> 14:56.591
No, I can't.

14:56.634 --> 14:58.332
My dad always wanted me
to help him in the garage,

14:58.375 --> 15:00.595
but I was always too clumsy,
too slow,

15:00.638 --> 15:01.944
too weak.

15:01.988 --> 15:03.119
"You gonna dry those tears
with your skirt,

15:03.163 --> 15:05.252
Drew Barrymore?"

15:05.948 --> 15:07.950
We should've just
paid Roy to fix it.

15:07.994 --> 15:11.258
Drew, trust me, you can do this.

15:14.087 --> 15:15.436
Fine.

15:15.479 --> 15:18.656
Good. There you go.

15:18.700 --> 15:20.049
Use some elbow grease on it.

15:20.093 --> 15:23.183
Now you tell me.
Where's the elbow grease?

15:26.490 --> 15:27.970
Hey.Hey.

15:28.014 --> 15:29.711
Can we talk for a second?

15:29.754 --> 15:34.107
Certainly. These characters are
waiting for Godot; so shall I.

15:35.325 --> 15:36.674
Um...

15:37.937 --> 15:39.634
You mentioned that

15:39.677 --> 15:42.550
Kyle was married to a woman
named Holly.

15:42.593 --> 15:45.466
Lovely woman.
What about her?

15:46.815 --> 15:48.251
Well, I talked to Kyle

15:48.295 --> 15:52.125
and he said they got a divorce
a couple years ago.

15:53.561 --> 15:57.782
A-Absolutely correct.
Yes, years ago.

15:57.826 --> 15:58.914
Tragic.

15:58.958 --> 16:00.307
Peter?Hmm?

16:01.786 --> 16:04.964
You kind of made it seem
like they were still together.

16:05.007 --> 16:07.488
[stammers]
There must have been some

16:07.531 --> 16:11.013
miscommunication because
they did indeed get divorced.

16:12.058 --> 16:15.975
There are things that we can do
to help you with your memory.

16:16.018 --> 16:17.237
I don't need help!

16:17.280 --> 16:18.803
If my memory were so bad,

16:18.847 --> 16:21.284
would I remember that
your birthday is April 5th?

16:21.328 --> 16:23.373
Or that Harry played

16:23.417 --> 16:25.114
college baseball
for Wisconsin?

16:25.158 --> 16:28.378
Or that Bette made out
with Gene Simmons in an IHOP?

16:28.422 --> 16:30.511
I just want to make sure
you're okay.

16:30.554 --> 16:32.556
You mean that I'm not
a feeble old man

16:32.600 --> 16:35.255
who can't button up
his own pants!

16:35.298 --> 16:37.213
That's what you mean!

16:41.696 --> 16:43.132
Can we talk for a minute?

16:43.176 --> 16:44.699
Yeah. Sure.

16:44.742 --> 16:47.136
What's going on? Why
are you avoiding me?

16:47.180 --> 16:49.486
W-W-What are you
talking about?

16:49.530 --> 16:51.184
Well, I thought we had
a good time on our date.

16:51.227 --> 16:53.925
But now every time I go
into a room, you leave.

16:53.969 --> 16:56.276
That's just a coincidence.

16:56.319 --> 16:58.104
You walked out
of a bowl game.

16:58.147 --> 17:00.193
There was a woman referee.

17:00.236 --> 17:02.325
I could no longer
trust the outcome.

17:02.369 --> 17:04.066
Spencer.

17:06.547 --> 17:08.288
All right.

17:09.158 --> 17:13.510
Actually,
I had a great time, too.

17:13.554 --> 17:16.948
You're sweet, you're fun,
you're sexy as hell.

17:16.992 --> 17:19.212
I know all this,
cut to the chase.

17:20.387 --> 17:24.173
The truth is I haven't...

17:24.217 --> 17:30.353
you know, been with anybody else
since my wife died.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.138
Oh.

17:32.181 --> 17:37.099
When you kissed me,
I guess I sort of freaked out.

17:37.143 --> 17:39.536
Well, why didn't
you tell me that?

17:39.580 --> 17:41.364
It's embarrassing.

17:41.408 --> 17:43.149
"I'm sad about my dead wife."

17:43.192 --> 17:45.716
It's not much of a turn-on.

17:45.760 --> 17:47.066
It's cute that I
make you nervous.

17:47.109 --> 17:49.111
You really do.

17:49.155 --> 17:52.027
I just wondered if maybe

17:52.071 --> 17:55.030
we couldn't slow it down
a little bit.

17:55.074 --> 17:58.077
You mean like hand stuff?

18:02.081 --> 18:07.173
I mean, like maybe we go out
to a movie or just hang out.

18:07.216 --> 18:12.265
Get to know each other a little
better. Then see where it goes.

18:12.308 --> 18:15.659
Mm, that'd be nice.

18:17.618 --> 18:20.577
I hate that I'm turning myself
into your gal pal.

18:20.621 --> 18:23.798
Hopefully our periods
don't start to sync up.

18:23.841 --> 18:27.628
I don't think that's gonna be
a problem for either of us.

18:32.981 --> 18:34.243
All right.

18:34.287 --> 18:36.593
Now screw on the cap

18:36.637 --> 18:38.639
and start 'er up.

18:38.682 --> 18:40.902
Righty tighty.

18:40.945 --> 18:44.427
And then in my version,
it would be "lefty incorrect-y."

18:44.471 --> 18:46.429
Start the damn thing.

18:48.127 --> 18:49.650
[engine starts]

18:49.693 --> 18:51.130
[chuckles]

18:51.173 --> 18:52.261
The "Check Engine" light
is off.

18:52.305 --> 18:53.567
And it's not smoking!

18:53.610 --> 18:55.960
[laughs]:
Oh, my God. I did it.

18:56.004 --> 18:57.440
I did it!

18:57.484 --> 18:58.702
Attaboy!

18:59.703 --> 19:01.140
You did it.

19:01.183 --> 19:02.402
Wait, what about your back?

19:02.445 --> 19:04.839
I'm feeling a lot better.

19:04.882 --> 19:08.277
You son of a so-and-so.
You were faking it.

19:08.321 --> 19:10.366
Yeah, but you fixed the van,
didn't ya?

19:10.410 --> 19:11.541
Because you believed in me.

19:11.585 --> 19:13.543
In spite of my best instincts.

19:14.849 --> 19:15.806
I'm proud of you.

19:15.850 --> 19:18.766
It does feel pretty good.Mm-hmm.

19:18.809 --> 19:20.376
So, what do you say?

19:20.420 --> 19:22.030
Am I a car guy now?

19:22.073 --> 19:24.206
[yelps]:
Oh!

19:24.250 --> 19:26.382
No. No, you're not.

19:33.868 --> 19:35.913
Hey, Peter! It's Gina!

19:35.957 --> 19:39.439
I brought you some apology
oatmeal raisin cookies.

19:39.482 --> 19:42.093
The raisins represent
forgiveness,

19:42.137 --> 19:45.706
'cause they're grapes
with a second chance.

19:47.925 --> 19:49.623
Peter?

19:50.972 --> 19:52.756
Peter?

19:53.931 --> 19:55.585
[beeps]

20:12.080 --> 20:14.082
[quietly]:Oh...
